Fonctions personnalises

Les trois fonctions suivantes seront utilises par la suite pour de la tokenisation de nos mots suivant les ngram, n tant le nombre de mots successifs.

BigramTokenizer <- function(x) {RWeka::NGramTokenizer(x, RWeka::Weka_control(min=2, max=2))}
ThreegramTokenizer <- function(x) {RWeka::NGramTokenizer(x, RWeka::Weka_control(min=3, max=3))}
FourgramTokenizer <- function(x) {RWeka::NGramTokenizer(x, RWeka::Weka_control(min=4, max=4))}

Normalize sera utilise par la suite lors de la prdiction

normalize <- function(x) {
  y <- min(x)
  z <- max(x)
  temp <- x - y
  temp1 <- (z - y)
  temp2 <- temp / temp1
  return(temp2)
}

Clean corpus est une mthode utilise pour nettoyer notre corpus de documents. En somme, elle retire les caractres non latins, transforme tout le corpus en minuscule, retire les mots inutiles, et fait du word stemming.

clean_corpus <- function(corpus){
  #to lower, so that we forget about uppercase
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transformer(tolower))
    #anything that doesn't fit this pattern must be eradicated
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function(x, pattern) gsub(pattern, " ", x))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, toSpace, "[^a-zA-Z ]")
  
  #remove weird letters I found
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function(x, pattern) gsub(pattern, "", x))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, toSpace, "")
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function(x, pattern) gsub(pattern, "", x))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, toSpace, "")
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function(x, pattern) gsub(pattern, "", x))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, toSpace, "")
  toSpace <- content_transformer(function(x, pattern) gsub(pattern, "", x))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, toSpace, "")
  #Weird words I have never seen people use on the deep web
  weird=""
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, stripWhitespace)
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords, c("the","day","yes","yet", "like","","","","will", "sale","get", "good","also","best","can",  weird,  "and", stopwords("english") ))
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeNumbers)
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removePunctuation)
  
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, stemDocument, language = "english")
  #more words I have noticed after stemming
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords, c("onlin","ship","buy","s","rs","ab","g","com","flipkart","deliveri","cash","one","india","shop","read","set","print","new","page","come","requir","give","name","know","item","general","usd","t","red","question","add","final","take","want","see","around","discount","content","two"))
  return(corpus)
}

On cre par la suite une Document term matrix, matrice avec des descriptions en ligne et des termes en colonne. 0 si le terme nexiste pas, 1 si le terme existe. On cre galement une term document matrix, qui contient la transpose de la document term matrix. On nettoie les sparse terms, avec en paramtre 0.995. Ca veut dire que tout terme nexistant pas dans 0.005 des documents devra tre supprim. Ca permet dviter loverfitting et de rduire le nombre dinputs. On ne peut pas supprimer plus de termes, par contre, car le vocabulaire de la drogue est ultra spcifique. Les termes les moins frquents sont parfois les plus prcis, et les plus frquents sont parfois le bruit

#Document Term Matrix, because we need to be organized folk

On fait une petite manoeuvre pour claircir le futur graphe

Frquence bigram des non drogues

par(las=2) # make label text perpendicular to axis
par(mar=c(5,8,4,2)) # increase y-axis margin.
barplot(head(sums_nondrugs.2g,10), main="Frequency of bigrams", horiz=TRUE,
        names.arg=head(colnames(sums_nondrugs.2g),10),  cex.names=0.8)

Frquence trigram des non drogues

par(las=2) # make label text perpenicular to axis
par(mar=c(5,8,4,2)) # increase y-axis margin.
barplot(head(sums_nondrugs.3g,10), main="Frequency of trigrams", horiz=TRUE,
        names.arg=head(colnames(sums_nondrugs.3g),10),  cex.names=0.8)

Frquence fourgram des non drogues

par(las=2) # make label text perpendicular to axis
par(mar=c(5,8,4,2)) # increase y-axis margin.
barplot(head(sums_nondrugs.4g,10), main="Frequency of fourgrams", horiz=TRUE,
        names.arg=head(colnames(sums_nondrugs.4g),10),  cex.names=0.8)
